<p>An element which can be used to load localized resources from property files. Stringbundles should be placed inside a <span class="script">template.XULElem("stringbundleset")</span> element.</p>
<p>A property file is a list of property key-value pairs each on a separate line. The key and value is separated with an equals sign. For example, the following defines two properties:</p>
<pre class="eval">
message.displayError=An error occured trying to display this message
message.nameAlreadyUsed=The nameÂ %S is already being used by another account.
</pre>
<p>More information is available in the <a title="en/XUL_Tutorial/Property_Files" href="/en/XUL_Tutorial/Property_Files">XUL tutorial</a>.</p>
<div class="note">The "src" attribute accepts only absolute <em>chrome://</em> URLs (see bugs <a href="https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=133698" title="https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=133698" class="link-https">133698</a>, <a href="https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=26291" title="https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=26291" class="link-https">26291</a>)</div>
